SIMPLE: fordo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fordo
<hw>For*do"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fordon</ets>, AS. <ets>ford<?/n</ets>; pref. <ets>for-</ets> +
<ets>d<?/n</ets> to do. See <er>For-</er>, and <er>Do</er>, <pos>v.
i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To destroy; to undo; to ruin.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is the night⟦br⟧
That either makes me or <qex>fordoes</qex> me quite.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To overcome with fatigue; to exhaust.</def>
<rj><au>M. Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All with weary task <qex>fordone</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fordone</ent>⟦br⟧
